- But...

312
00:10:44,318 --> 00:10:46,228
- Right. We're handling...
- They cover all sports.

313
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:48,158
a lot of sports that our channel covers.

314
00:10:48,158 --> 00:10:50,098
But I usually handle baseball games,

315
00:10:50,098 --> 00:10:51,198
- volleyball games, - Volleyball.

316
00:10:51,528 --> 00:10:54,428
and short-track skating games in winter from time to time.

317
00:10:55,168 --> 00:10:57,698
When did you join the channel then?

318
00:10:57,698 --> 00:11:00,968
I've been working as a sportscaster for 13 years.

319
00:11:00,968 --> 00:11:03,438
But I joined SBS five years ago.

320
00:11:03,438 --> 00:11:04,638
Five years ago.

321
00:11:04,778 --> 00:11:06,408
What about you, Woo Young?

322
00:11:06,608 --> 00:11:08,248
Given that he's sitting in the center,

323
00:11:08,248 --> 00:11:09,578
I bet it's been 30 years for him.

324
00:11:09,918 --> 00:11:11,518
- How long has it been for you?
- How many years?

325
00:11:11,518 --> 00:11:13,348
- Twenty-three years.
- Twenty-three years.

326
00:11:14,848 --> 00:11:16,818
- All baseball fans know his voice.
- Gosh, no.

327
00:11:16,818 --> 00:11:18,058
- Right.
- Of course.

328
00:11:18,218 --> 00:11:20,288
I don't know much about baseball, but his voice already sounds...

329
00:11:20,288 --> 00:11:22,328
- That's right.
- so familiar.

330
00:11:22,528 --> 00:11:23,958
We were on a radio show together.

331
00:11:26,428 --> 00:11:28,328
(Hold on a minute.)

332
00:11:28,668 --> 00:11:30,038
- That happens sometimes.
- Wait.

333
00:11:30,138 --> 00:11:31,868
No, not sometimes. This happens a lot with her.

334
00:11:31,868 --> 00:11:33,108
- This is quite common with her.
- You know?

335
00:11:33,268 --> 00:11:35,168
- No wonder. You looked...
- Did he look familiar?

336
00:11:35,168 --> 00:11:37,278
- I... Hey. You...
- You said we should be friends.

337
00:11:40,008 --> 00:11:41,708
- Hey, Woo Young.
- Sook.

338
00:11:42,108 --> 00:11:45,018
- Sook. Why drop the honorifics?
- Woo Young!

339
00:11:45,418 --> 00:11:47,088
- Your face is so red.
- It's so red.

340
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:49,258
I'm friends with Woo Young.

341
00:11:49,588 --> 00:11:51,458
What happened, ZO ZAZZ?

342
00:11:51,858 --> 00:11:53,858
My gosh, Woo Young. Have you been well?

343
00:11:53,858 --> 00:11:54,988
I've been well.

344
00:11:55,358 --> 00:11:56,728
- Oh, right.
- But how did you...

345
00:11:56,728 --> 00:11:58,028
