- How did that happen?

346
00:11:58,198 --> 00:11:59,568
- Was it an SBS radio show?
- Yes.

347
00:11:59,568 --> 00:12:01,228
- Was it "Sisters' Radio?"
- Yes.

348
00:12:01,528 --> 00:12:03,268
- Then Eun I was there too.
- Yes, she was.

349
00:12:03,368 --> 00:12:04,638
- I was there too?
- Yes.

350
00:12:07,238 --> 00:12:09,038
Hey, you messed up big time.

351
00:12:09,738 --> 00:12:12,208
- You can't mess up like this.
- Eun I.

352
00:12:12,378 --> 00:12:13,608
- He looks younger...
- He's not wearing any makeup.

353
00:12:13,608 --> 00:12:14,848
and more handsome.

354
00:12:14,848 --> 00:12:16,178
Right. That's why we couldn't recognize you.

355
00:12:17,718 --> 00:12:19,548
I do remember him now. We were born in the same year.

356
00:12:20,318 --> 00:12:21,448
We were born in 1975.

357
00:12:21,448 --> 00:12:24,288
If he was born in 1975, he should be the department head. Right?

358
00:12:24,288 --> 00:12:25,688
- Right.
- He is the department head.

359
00:12:25,858 --> 00:12:27,958
- He's already become a legend...
- Gosh, no.

360
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:31,028
- among sportscasters.
- I see.

361
00:12:31,028 --> 00:12:32,568
- So are you the department head?
- He's sitting in the right spot.

362
00:12:32,568 --> 00:12:34,898
- Right. He picked the right spot.
- He's in the right spot.

363
00:12:35,098 --> 00:12:37,798
- He naturally found his spot.
- Yes. He got his spot.

364
00:12:37,898 --> 00:12:38,898
What's your title...

365
00:12:38,898 --> 00:12:40,608
- if you don't mind me asking?
- I'm the deputy head.

366
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,468
- The deputy head.
- The deputy head.

367
00:12:42,468 --> 00:12:44,008
I mean, we can't generalize the average age.

368
00:12:44,008 --> 00:12:45,978
But how old are you?

369
00:12:45,978 --> 00:12:47,308
I was born in 1990.

370
00:12:48,108 --> 00:12:50,378
- Then you got promoted fast.
- He got promoted at a young age.

371
00:12:50,678 --> 00:12:52,218
He joined the industry at a young age.

372
00:12:53,118 --> 00:12:54,488
I've been fulfilling tasks as a deputy head.

373
00:12:54,488 --> 00:12:55,818
I'll soon be promoted.

374
00:12:55,888 --> 00:12:57,818
- You'll be promoted soon.
- Yes.

375
00:12:58,158 --> 00:13:00,628
There's a substantial age gap between you guys. Right?

376
00:13:00,888 --> 00:13:02,798
- Are you guys close?
- I've been dreaming...

377
00:13:02,998 --> 00:13:05,698
to become a sportscaster while listening to his commentary.

378
00:13:05,698 --> 00:13:08,328
- Really?
- Now, we're both working at SBS.

379
00:13:08,568 --> 00:13:10,768
I must follow in his footsteps.

380
00:13:11,338 --> 00:13:12,368
(Surprised)

381
00:13:12,368 --> 00:13:14,068
He's buttering up his superior.

382
00:13:14,068 --> 00:13:15,438
(This is how a deputy head behaves in a work setting.)

383
00:13:15,438 --> 00:13:18,078
On top of that, he always...

384
00:13:18,938 --> 00:13:21,148
- He shows you the way.
- Of course. He does.

385
00:13:21,148 --> 00:13:23,178
- He guides you.
- He gives me a helping hand.

386
00:13:23,178 --> 00:13:24,848
- "Helping hand."
- He roots for you.

387
00:13:25,178 --> 00:13:27,518
- He encourages and helps you.
- You're rubbing your palms a lot.

388
00:13:27,688 --> 00:13:28,748
- Seriously.
- Gosh.

389
00:13:28,918 --> 00:13:30,058
You're rubbing your palms.

390
00:13:30,118 --> 00:13:32,588
- This is a sensitive topic.
- He hasn't been promoted yet.

391
00:13:32,588 --> 00:13:33,588
- It's before his promotion.
- He needs...

392
00:13:33,588 --> 00:13:34,758
- So he must be careful.
- to get promoted.

393
00:13:35,158 --> 00:13:36,558
To get promoted,

394
00:13:36,828 --> 00:13:38,798
- he has to be careful.
- He's good at his job.

395
00:13:39,428 --> 00:13:41,528
But I meant everything I said.

396
00:13:41,528 --> 00:13:43,868
- I respect him a lot.
- Of course.

397
00:13:43,968 --> 00:13:45,138
He tries out...

398
00:13:45,138 --> 00:13:47,308
a lot of new expressions among baseball commentators.

399
00:13:47,308 --> 00:13:48,838
- Exactly.
- He's a pioneer.

400
00:13:49,508 --> 00:13:51,008
Could you give us an example?

401
00:13:51,478 --> 00:13:55,408
It was during the 5th game of the playoffs in 2018.

402
00:13:55,748 --> 00:13:58,318
When Han Yoo Seom did a walk-off home run,

403
00:13:58,318 --> 00:14:01,218
I said "goodbye" three times.

404
00:14:01,218 --> 00:14:03,258
- He said it before Hwasa.
- Right.

405
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,788
- He hits the ball.
- There.

406
00:14:06,858 --> 00:14:08,388
(The ball...)

407
00:14:08,388 --> 00:14:09,828
(is flying...)

408
00:14:09,828 --> 00:14:11,928
(to Jamsil!)

409
00:14:12,058 --> 00:14:16,338
(Goodbye!)

410
00:14:16,338 --> 00:14:18,398
- It was the walk-off home run.
- It was the walk-off home run.

411
00:14:18,398 --> 00:14:19,868
- It ended the game.
- The home run ended the series.

412
00:14:19,868 --> 00:14:20,938
- Right.
- Yes.

413
00:14:20,938 --> 00:14:22,568
I've tried many different expressions.

414
00:14:22,568 --> 00:14:24,608
Here's the style I tried in 2025.

415
00:14:25,008 --> 00:14:26,708
- When there were three syllables, - Yes.

416
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:27,948
I spoke in a staccato-style.

417
00:14:28,278 --> 00:14:29,548
- Staccato?
- How?

418
00:14:29,648 --> 00:14:31,048
If it was a back-to-back home run,

419
00:14:31,048 --> 00:14:32,948
I said, "back to back."

420
00:14:33,648 --> 00:14:36,188
- So there was an intention.
- "Back to back."

421
00:14:36,758 --> 00:14:38,458
How did that go? Was it well-received?

422
00:14:38,788 --> 00:14:39,928
I didn't get any reaction.

423
00:14:40,188 --> 00:14:41,728
(Laughing)

424
00:14:41,728 --> 00:14:43,998
I just found out that he tried to make this style popular.

425
00:14:43,998 --> 00:14:46,928
- Really?
- He came up with an idea for 2025.

426
00:14:47,328 --> 00:14:48,398
How about you?

427
00:14:48,528 --> 00:14:51,598
I often try to use literary expressions...

428
00:14:51,768 --> 00:14:53,708
- when I commentate.
- I'm curious.

429
00:14:53,938 --> 00:14:56,808
- He majored in Korean Literature.
- I majored in Korean Literature.

430
00:14:56,878 --> 00:14:57,908
- Really?
- Yes.

431
00:14:57,908 --> 00:15:00,778
When they hit a home run, I often say,

432
00:15:00,778 --> 00:15:02,448
"into the distance."

433
00:15:02,448 --> 00:15:04,748
- "Into the distance."
- "Into the distance."

434
00:15:05,678 --> 00:15:07,918
(Into the distance,)

435
00:15:08,118 --> 00:15:11,118
(it goes!)

436
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:13,358
Here's why. Considering Korean linguistics,

437
00:15:13,488 --> 00:15:15,028
the expression has long sounds.

438
00:15:15,028 --> 00:15:17,358
So it highlights the rhythm nicely.

439
00:15:17,898 --> 00:15:19,628
I thought it'd leave an impression on the viewers.

440
00:15:20,328 --> 00:15:22,868
But I doubt the baseball fans recognized my effort.

441
00:15:23,198 --> 00:15:24,238
(Laughing)

442
00:15:24,238 --> 00:15:25,898
Both of them tried, but the fans didn't know.

443
00:15:25,938 --> 00:15:29,708
It would be better if you used expressions with more impact.

444
00:15:29,708 --> 00:15:30,908
(Like what?)

445
00:15:30,908 --> 00:15:32,678
"It's understandable..."

446
00:15:33,248 --> 00:15:34,778
(Surprised)

447
00:15:35,508 --> 00:15:37,618
I think Kyeong Hwan's catchphrases might suit...

448
00:15:37,618 --> 00:15:38,848
baseball games well.

449
00:15:39,018 --> 00:15:41,188
- "Unfortunately..."
- "Unfortunately..."

450
00:15:42,218 --> 00:15:43,518
- "Fortunately..."
- He has a lot of catchphrases.

451
00:15:43,688 --> 00:15:46,288
- "The ball is flying over now."
- "It's flying over now."

452
00:15:46,658 --> 00:15:48,858
- "Double plays are not allowed."
- "They're not allowed."

453
00:15:49,498 --> 00:15:51,058
- Everything works.
- They do.

454
00:15:51,058 --> 00:15:52,258
Everything works.

455
00:15:52,258 --> 00:15:53,828
- Those are nice options.
- Right.

456
00:15:54,298 --> 00:15:55,698
- We'll give them a try.
- Great.

457
00:15:55,968 --> 00:15:59,808
Did one of you apply to be on our show?

458
00:16:00,068 --> 00:16:01,208
Yes, it was me.

459
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,808
- Really? You did?
- My friend did it.

460
00:16:02,808 --> 00:16:03,838
- Yes.
- Okay.

461
00:16:04,108 --> 00:16:06,778
My wife is a huge fan of the show.

462
00:16:07,248 --> 00:16:09,418
She loves the show. So she watches every episode.

463
00:16:09,418 --> 00:16:10,648
- Really?
- Yes.

464
00:16:10,648 --> 00:16:13,018
And I've witnessed a lot of miraculous moments...

465
00:16:13,018 --> 00:16:14,948
while commentating on games.

466
00:16:14,948 --> 00:16:16,388
- I'm sure.
- Yes.

467
00:16:16,388 --> 00:16:19,488
But I particularly remember Cha Seung Won's episode.

468
00:16:19,488 --> 00:16:20,588
(The episode with Cha Seung Won and Gong Myoung)

469
00:16:20,628 --> 00:16:21,988
- He hit 3 in 1 shot.
- He hit 3 in 1 shot.

470
00:16:24,428 --> 00:16:25,558
- My gosh.
- Oh, my!

471
00:16:25,558 --> 00:16:28,098
(It was a miraculous moment.)

472
00:16:28,698 --> 00:16:29,838
(He's still amazed by it.)

473
00:16:29,838 --> 00:16:31,368
- Seriously.
- That was crazy.

474
00:16:31,368 --> 00:16:32,538
What a thrill.

475
00:16:33,408 --> 00:16:34,708
- His eyes got bigger.
- Yes.

476
00:16:35,268 --> 00:16:38,178
I thought this went beyond sports. That's what I thought.

477
00:16:38,178 --> 00:16:39,408
- Really?
- Yes.

478
00:16:39,508 --> 00:16:42,978
One of the key elements our viewers look for in our show...

479
00:16:42,978 --> 00:16:44,378
- is the thrill.
- Yes.

480
00:16:44,518 --> 00:16:46,148
But they also like saying things, "Those fools."

481
00:16:47,148 --> 00:16:48,188
- "They are clueless."
- They like to criticize.

482
00:16:48,188 --> 00:16:49,858
- "Gosh, look at them."
- "Those fools."

483
00:16:49,858 --> 00:16:51,858
"My gosh, they can't even do that?"

484
00:16:51,858 --> 00:16:53,528
- Exactly.
- Right.

485
00:16:54,358 --> 00:16:56,128
It'd be nice if they could commentate...

486
00:16:56,128 --> 00:16:57,858
while we play games today.

487
00:16:57,858 --> 00:16:59,568
- He says that often.
- Sounds great.

488
00:16:59,568 --> 00:17:01,828
- He often talks about your show.
