00:39:44,538 --> 00:39:46,098
- Bro gets three.
- Okay.

1244
00:39:46,098 --> 00:39:47,638
- Got it.
- Don't worry, Yeon Seok.

1245
00:39:47,638 --> 00:39:49,268
- People call her "bro."
- It's nothing new.

1246
00:39:49,268 --> 00:39:51,278
- People often call her "bro."
- It's nothing new.

1247
00:39:51,538 --> 00:39:53,478
Bro Sook gets 3. Bro Song gets 3.

1248
00:39:53,478 --> 00:39:55,348
- Okay.
- Three, three, and four.

1249
00:39:55,348 --> 00:39:56,708
- Three, three, and four.
- Bro Song and Bro Sook.

1250
00:39:56,708 --> 00:39:57,818
- Three, three, and four.
- Three, three, and four.

1251
00:39:58,718 --> 00:40:00,948
Ready. Set.

1252
00:40:02,118 --> 00:40:04,858
(9th try)

1253
00:40:04,858 --> 00:40:05,888
Amazing.

1254
00:40:06,888 --> 00:40:07,958
- Oh, no.
- Just one.

1255
00:40:07,958 --> 00:40:09,688
(9th try)

1256
00:40:09,688 --> 00:40:12,358
- What a bad shot.
- All right.

1257
00:40:12,358 --> 00:40:13,758
The first one should've been hit.

1258
00:40:14,168 --> 00:40:20,538
(9th try)

1259
00:40:21,068 --> 00:40:22,138
That was a nice hit.

1260
00:40:22,138 --> 00:40:24,608
(9th try)

1261
00:40:24,608 --> 00:40:25,908
- Ten seconds left.
- Ten seconds?

1262
00:40:27,338 --> 00:40:28,908
- Oh, no.
- Again, Jae Suk?

1263
00:40:29,208 --> 00:40:31,018
- You're too tense.
- Calm down.

1264
00:40:31,218 --> 00:40:32,248
Just hit it.

1265
00:40:32,448 --> 00:40:34,718
- We're short on time. Come on.
- Three, two,

1266
00:40:34,948 --> 00:40:36,018
one.

1267
00:40:36,018 --> 00:40:37,618
(Failed without reaching the bottles)

1268
00:40:37,618 --> 00:40:40,258
Jae Suk gets nervous the moment he enters the box.

1269
00:40:40,258 --> 00:40:41,888
Why do you get so hyper?

1270
00:40:42,058 --> 00:40:44,058
- It's that...
- He gets tense.

1271
00:40:44,228 --> 00:40:46,898
Why do I only get ten seconds?

1272
00:40:46,898 --> 00:40:49,168
I watched him from the back.

1273
00:40:49,428 --> 00:40:50,668
When he entered the box,

1274
00:40:50,798 --> 00:40:52,598
I knew he couldn't make it.

1275
00:40:52,598 --> 00:40:54,408
- I just knew it.
- Think about it.

1276
00:40:54,638 --> 00:40:56,008
Everyone gets ten seconds.

1277
00:40:56,438 --> 00:40:59,708
- You equally got 10 seconds.
- Don't say "10 seconds left."

1278
00:41:00,278 --> 00:41:02,908
Say it when there's five seconds left.

1279
00:41:03,878 --> 00:41:05,818
The third batter was all tensed up.

1280
00:41:06,248 --> 00:41:07,948
- This time...
- It's our last try.

1281
00:41:07,948 --> 00:41:09,118
- From what I see...
- You two...

1282
00:41:09,118 --> 00:41:10,718
- Yes?
- Because...

1283
00:41:10,718 --> 00:41:11,758
I'll throw the balls.

1284
00:41:11,758 --> 00:41:13,618
- Yes, like earlier.
- Let's do it as earlier.

1285
00:41:13,758 --> 00:41:15,358
- When we succeeded.
- It's our last try.

1286
00:41:15,358 --> 00:41:16,788
- Let's cheer.
- Let's go.

1287
00:41:16,928 --> 00:41:18,028
- Here.
- Gather up.

1288
00:41:18,028 --> 00:41:19,128
Let's make a miracle.

1289
00:41:19,298 --> 00:41:20,398
- In 1, 2, 3.
- In 1, 2, 3.

1290
00:41:20,398 --> 00:41:21,598
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

1291
00:41:21,598 --> 00:41:22,868
My hands are sweaty.

1292
00:41:22,868 --> 00:41:25,038
- You're right. You sweat a lot.
- Really?

1293
00:41:25,038 --> 00:41:26,368
I don't get this sweaty...

1294
00:41:26,368 --> 00:41:28,108
- even during coverage.
- Your hands are covered in sweat.

1295
00:41:28,368 --> 00:41:29,368
My hands stay dry...

1296
00:41:29,368 --> 00:41:30,368
- even during good games.
- For real?

1297
00:41:30,468 --> 00:41:32,138
It's because the game is interesting.

1298
00:41:32,138 --> 00:41:33,378
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1299
00:41:33,378 --> 00:41:34,508
- We can do it.
- Good luck.

1300
00:41:34,608 --> 00:41:35,678
We can do it.

1301
00:41:35,908 --> 00:41:37,548
- At least hit one, Eun I.
- Go front.

1302
00:41:37,548 --> 00:41:39,178
(With the lineup that succeeded Round 2)

1303
00:41:39,178 --> 00:41:40,648
Four? All set.

1304
00:41:40,648 --> 00:41:42,748
(Came together again with 2 outs in the bottom of the 9th)

1305
00:41:42,748 --> 00:41:44,588
The last try. Ready.

1306
00:41:44,588 --> 00:41:45,758
(Out of 10 total tries, they're on try number 10.)

1307
00:41:45,758 --> 00:41:46,818
Set.

1308
00:41:48,188 --> 00:41:49,688
(Last try)

1309
00:41:49,688 --> 00:41:50,728
- One.
- Oh, dear.

1310
00:41:50,898 --> 00:41:51,958
A little lower.

1311
00:41:52,128 --> 00:41:53,498
- Two.
- Nice.

1312
00:41:53,598 --> 00:41:54,898
- All good.
- That was close.

1313
00:41:54,898 --> 00:41:56,298
- Here.
- Not bad.

1314
00:41:56,298 --> 00:41:57,968
- It's okay.
- It's okay. One last ball.

1315
00:41:59,068 --> 00:42:00,968
- A swing and miss.
- One more.

1316
00:42:00,968 --> 00:42:02,738
- You did four.
- A swing and miss.

1317
00:42:02,908 --> 00:42:04,068
- I did four, right?
- Five.

1318
00:42:04,068 --> 00:42:05,838
- You did 5.
- I did 5?

1319
00:42:05,838 --> 00:42:07,508
(Last try)

1320
00:42:07,508 --> 00:42:08,548
Nice one.

1321
00:42:08,548 --> 00:42:10,748
(Got rid of one)

1322
00:42:11,878 --> 00:42:13,778
- That's it.
- Nice, Yeon Seok.

1323
00:42:13,778 --> 00:42:14,948
Ten seconds left.

1324
00:42:14,948 --> 00:42:16,948
Sook.

1325
00:42:16,948 --> 00:42:18,018
All right.

1326
00:42:18,418 --> 00:42:20,118
- A walk-off!
- Bottom of the 9th, 2 outs.

1327
00:42:20,118 --> 00:42:21,428
- Bottom of the 9th, 2 outs.
- Just one.

1328
00:42:21,958 --> 00:42:23,028
Three.

1329
00:42:24,928 --> 00:42:29,028
(The last ball has been thrown!)

1330
00:42:29,298 --> 00:42:30,898
Three, two...

1331
00:42:32,038 --> 00:42:35,068
(The end of the game)

1332
00:42:35,508 --> 00:42:36,508
Two...

1333
00:42:36,508 --> 00:42:39,138
(Both plop down.)

1334
00:42:40,808 --> 00:42:43,078
- Oh, no.
- Oh, no.

1335
00:42:43,448 --> 00:42:44,518
It's okay.

1336
00:42:46,678 --> 00:42:47,948
No.

1337
00:42:48,148 --> 00:42:49,188
Wait a minute.

1338
00:42:54,058 --> 00:42:55,958
They must be the fastest people.

1339
00:42:55,958 --> 00:42:57,858
(The prizes are collected fast.)

1340
00:42:57,858 --> 00:42:59,328
- Listen.
- They're gone.

1341
00:43:00,128 --> 00:43:01,728
I told you to take the neckties.

1342
00:43:01,728 --> 00:43:03,168
You should've stopped at Round Two.

1343
00:43:03,168 --> 00:43:04,238
No.

1344
00:43:04,838 --> 00:43:06,268
We had so much fun.

1345
00:43:06,268 --> 00:43:08,068
- I told you.
- It was fun.

1346
00:43:08,068 --> 00:43:09,568
- Really?
- Yes.

1347
00:43:09,568 --> 00:43:11,078
We had a blast.

1348
00:43:11,078 --> 00:43:13,238
What a bummer.

1349
00:43:14,348 --> 00:43:15,378
That bottle is annoying.

1350
00:43:15,378 --> 00:43:18,278
If only there were another miracle.

1351
00:43:18,678 --> 00:43:19,818
Sports games don't always end...

1352
00:43:19,818 --> 00:43:20,918
- with a happy ending.
- Exactly.

1353
00:43:20,918 --> 00:43:23,018
- Here. It's a bummer.
- At least take the goodie bag.

1354
00:43:23,248 --> 00:43:25,418
- I can't forget about the neckties.
- Right?

1355
00:43:25,418 --> 00:43:27,218
- They were excited about them.
- It's okay.

1356
00:43:27,318 --> 00:43:30,058
But wearing them would have boosted the class of our show.

1357
00:43:30,958 --> 00:43:32,198
(The luxurious neckties passed by.)

1358
00:43:32,198 --> 00:43:33,258
- Round Two...
- Gosh.

1359
00:43:33,528 --> 00:43:35,568
Either way, thank you to the two...

1360
00:43:35,798 --> 00:43:37,568
- for joining us.
- Right.

1361
00:43:37,568 --> 00:43:41,068
It's a bummer, but we had fun, thanks to you.

1362
00:43:41,368 --> 00:43:42,708
Thank you.

1363
00:43:42,708 --> 00:43:45,438
- Good job.
- Baseball season will soon return.

1364
00:43:45,438 --> 00:43:47,508
- Right.
- We look forward...

1365
00:43:47,508 --> 00:43:48,808
to your coverage.

1366
00:43:49,208 --> 00:43:51,378
- Whenever possible...
- Into the distance...

1367
00:43:51,748 --> 00:43:53,378
We will see you outside the fence.

1368
00:43:55,518 --> 00:43:58,358
How disappointing. It leaves you feeling empty.

1369
00:43:58,358 --> 00:44:00,258
(How disappointing. It leaves you feeling empty.)

1370
00:44:01,088 --> 00:44:04,158
(Unfortunately failed Round 3)

1371
00:44:04,158 --> 00:44:05,228
What a bummer.

1372
00:44:07,028 --> 00:44:08,328
I could've played a critical role.

1373
00:44:08,328 --> 00:44:09,398
One... Sorry?

1374
00:44:11,268 --> 00:44:13,298
I couldn't make even one vision in my head come true.

1375
00:44:13,298 --> 00:44:15,008
(The star-crossed player who couldn't play his part)

1376
00:44:15,608 --> 00:44:16,868
We should've stopped at Round Two.

1377
00:44:16,968 --> 00:44:17,978
Without a doubt. Your friend was...

1378
00:44:17,978 --> 00:44:19,238
- really greedy.
- Very greedy.

1379
00:44:19,808 --> 00:44:21,478
He had a sudden rush of dopamine.

1380
00:44:21,478 --> 00:44:22,578
- Right.
- He couldn't stop.

1381
00:44:22,578 --> 00:44:24,078
- Right.
- He's addicted to dopamine.

1382
00:44:24,078 --> 00:44:25,818
The brothers did so well, though.

1383
00:44:25,948 --> 00:44:27,818
- Are you talking about us?
- Yes.

1384
00:44:27,818 --> 00:44:29,288
- You did great.
- Anyway, we should...

1385
00:44:29,288 --> 00:44:31,858
Yes, let's get going. We'll have to move for a while.

1386
00:44:31,858 --> 00:44:32,988
How far is it?

1387
00:44:32,988 --> 00:44:35,228
- Let's see.
- Is it minus 10°C outside?

1388
00:44:35,228 --> 00:44:36,228
Minus 11.

1389
00:44:37,428 --> 00:44:39,628
(Minus 11°C)

1390
00:44:40,028 --> 00:44:43,568
(Still, I am)

1391
00:44:43,998 --> 00:44:47,238
(Waiting for you)

1392
00:44:47,908 --> 00:44:51,378
(To the next spare spot, I'll go with you)

1393
00:44:51,378 --> 00:44:52,808
- Can you hurry up?
- I found it.

1394
00:44:53,838 --> 00:44:54,878
I found it.

1395
00:44:55,308 --> 00:44:57,608
The bus stop is about five minutes away.

1396
00:44:57,608 --> 00:44:59,318
- Really? Shall we go?
- Let's get going.

1397
00:44:59,318 --> 00:45:00,548
What time do we have to get there?

1398
00:45:00,648 --> 00:45:01,818
At 12pm?

1399
00:45:01,848 --> 00:45:03,448
Then, we have just enough time for lunch.

1400
00:45:03,448 --> 00:45:04,518
- Yes.
- We should eat first.

1401
00:45:04,518 --> 00:45:06,288
- We have to eat first.
- We should.

1402
00:45:06,718 --> 00:45:08,628
- But I can't eat.
- Why not?

1403
00:45:08,788 --> 00:45:10,058
She has an endoscopy tomorrow.

1404
00:45:10,188 --> 00:45:11,998
- Then...
- Oh, no.

1405
00:45:11,998 --> 00:45:14,568
- Up and down both.
- Up and down both.

1406
00:45:14,768 --> 00:45:17,228
(Gastroscopy and colonoscopy)

1407
00:45:17,228 --> 00:45:18,468
- Colonoscopy and...
- That's...

1408
00:45:18,468 --> 00:45:19,638
- You know what?
- Yes.

1409
00:45:19,668 --> 00:45:20,768
Sook shouldn't eat.

1410
00:45:20,768 --> 00:45:21,938
- Okay.
- She's fine with that.

1411
00:45:21,938 --> 00:45:23,108
I'll just have plain porridge.

1412
00:45:23,108 --> 00:45:24,138
Yes.

1413
00:45:24,138 --> 00:45:25,638
- We'll grill some meat, then.
- Eat something delicious.

1414
00:45:25,638 --> 00:45:26,638
That sounds good.

1415
00:45:26,638 --> 00:45:27,808
(Exclaiming)

1416
00:45:28,308 --> 00:45:30,448
- Is that too much?
- You're cruel, Mr. Grasshopper.

1417
00:45:31,448 --> 00:45:32,548
You've changed.

1418
00:45:33,048 --> 00:45:34,178
Mr. Grasshopper.

1419
00:45:34,178 --> 00:45:35,188
(He doesn't care.)

1420
00:45:35,188 --> 00:45:36,548
- We...
- He's not like that anywhere else.

1421
00:45:36,548 --> 00:45:37,548
He does that only when he's with us.

1422
00:45:37,548 --> 00:45:39,018
He used to be so kind.

1423
00:45:39,658 --> 00:45:42,058
You were so gentle. What made you so vicious?

1424
00:45:42,428 --> 00:45:43,788
She and I used to smoke together.

1425
00:45:43,788 --> 00:45:45,528
- Stop talking about that.
- Smoking buds.

1426
00:45:45,528 --> 00:45:46,958
- Yes, smoking buds.
- Smoking friends.

1427
00:45:46,958 --> 00:45:47,968
Smoking buds?

1428
00:45:48,068 --> 00:45:50,268
- The SFs.
- Smoking friends?

1429
00:45:50,768 --> 00:45:52,438
- We can eat on the way.
- Yes, let's go.

1430
00:45:52,438 --> 00:45:54,508
Our main writer and second writer.

1431
00:45:55,438 --> 00:45:59,138
The meeting is over, so let's have lunch.

1432
00:45:59,138 --> 00:46:00,378
Where do you want to go, Director?

1433
00:46:00,378 --> 00:46:01,548
(Director Yoo of the TV network)

1434
00:46:01,548 --> 00:46:04,378
- We...
- And we have the new producer.

1435
00:46:04,378 --> 00:46:05,978
- Wait.
- You should work together.

1436
00:46:05,978 --> 00:46:07,078
- Do you know a place around here?
- Ms. Song.

1437
00:46:07,078 --> 00:46:09,848
- Ms. Song, can you...
- Sorry to bother you again.

1438
00:46:10,348 --> 00:46:12,588
Yes, in Sangam-dong. From the show last time.

1439
00:46:12,588 --> 00:46:15,288
- Send me the address.
- These writers and I...

1440
00:46:15,288 --> 00:46:16,888
go way back.

1441
00:46:16,988 --> 00:46:18,058
Producer Yoo.

1442
00:46:18,058 --> 00:46:19,428
- We go way back.
- They're veterans, aren't they?

1443
00:46:19,428 --> 00:46:20,528
Obviously.

1444
00:46:20,528 --> 00:46:22,598
They're practically the spirits of Sangam-dong.

1445
00:46:23,098 --> 00:46:24,598
I participated in a lot of shows...

1446
00:46:24,598 --> 00:46:26,298
before they built these buildings here.

1447
00:46:26,998 --> 00:46:28,768
- When these were just fields.
- Nothing but fields.

1448
00:46:29,908 --> 00:46:31,708
There was literally nothing back in the day.

1449
00:46:31,708 --> 00:46:32,808
- Nothing.
- It was literally a plain.

1450
00:46:32,808 --> 00:46:33,808
- Right.
- It was.

1451
00:46:34,008 --> 00:46:36,078
This area and Magok-dong have changed the most.

1452
00:46:36,078 --> 00:46:37,978
- Magok.
- Yes, Magok too.

1453
00:46:38,478 --> 00:46:41,518
Old people say that a lot.

1454
00:46:41,518 --> 00:46:43,988
"There were only farms in Gangnam back in the day."

1455
00:46:43,988 --> 00:46:45,188
"These were all pear orchards."

1456
00:46:45,618 --> 00:46:46,688
And we...

1457
00:46:46,688 --> 00:46:48,728
- And we heard that.
- We heard that.

1458
00:46:49,328 --> 00:46:51,028
Our seniors always said things...

1459
00:46:51,028 --> 00:46:52,828
- that we didn't understand.
- Right.

1460
00:46:52,828 --> 00:46:54,198
- The old stories.
- "Back in the day,"

1461
00:46:54,198 --> 00:46:55,828
"in that studio in Gyeongungung Palace..."

1462
00:46:55,828 --> 00:46:57,868
You're right. The one in Anguk-dong.

1463
00:46:57,868 --> 00:47:00,038
I was like, "Why is there a studio in Gyeongungung Palace?"

1464
00:47:00,038 --> 00:47:01,108
Right.

1465
00:47:01,108 --> 00:47:02,308
- That's true.
- And when we...

1466
00:47:02,308 --> 00:47:04,838
talk about MBC in Yeouido, the juniors go,

1467
00:47:04,838 --> 00:47:06,738
- "MBC was in Yeouido?"
- "MBC in Yeouido?"

1468
00:47:06,738 --> 00:47:09,148
Or, "All the dramas were aired live back in the day."

1469
00:47:09,148 --> 00:47:10,408
You're right.

1470
00:47:11,248 --> 00:47:12,578
"The dramas were aired live?"

1471
00:47:12,578 --> 00:47:14,148
- "Yes!"
- And we're...

1472
00:47:14,148 --> 00:47:16,448
- at their age now.
- "That's how we did it."

1473
00:47:17,388 --> 00:47:19,018
This is...

1474
00:47:19,018 --> 00:47:20,118
(The youngest member in his early 40s is busy searching.)

1475
00:47:20,188 --> 00:47:21,588
Where are we going, by the way?

1476
00:47:21,588 --> 00:47:23,258
- Where are we going?
- We're following Yeon Seok.

1477
00:47:23,758 --> 00:47:24,958
What do you think about leaf wraps and rice?

1478
00:47:24,958 --> 00:47:26,098
- Great!
- I like that.

1479
00:47:26,098 --> 00:47:27,868
- I can't wait to eat it.
- It's back there.

1480
00:47:28,298 --> 00:47:30,068
In front of JTBC. On the second floor.

1481
00:47:30,068 --> 00:47:31,338
- Let's go.
- You know right away.

1482
00:47:31,338 --> 00:47:32,598
- Yes, that's it.
- I'm dying to eat it.

1483
00:47:32,798 --> 00:47:34,198
- Leaf wraps and rice?
- It sounds great.

1484
00:47:34,198 --> 00:47:35,838
- Leaf wraps and rice?
- Leaf wraps and rice!

1485
00:47:36,868 --> 00:47:40,178
(The leaf wraps and rice dance)

1486
00:47:40,178 --> 00:47:41,848
- You used that to dance?
- You didn't see it coming?

1487
00:47:41,848 --> 00:47:43,878
- I never knew.
- No way.

1488
00:47:43,878 --> 00:47:46,618
- You should have played along.
- You had to.

1489
00:47:46,748 --> 00:47:48,848
- Leaf wraps and rice?
- Leaf wraps and rice!

1490
00:47:49,588 --> 00:47:53,488
(Encore)

1491
00:47:54,288 --> 00:47:56,358
- You guys are truly comedians.
- You bet.

1492
00:47:56,588 --> 00:47:58,128
These are true comedians.

1493
00:47:58,358 --> 00:48:00,058
- Teach him more.
- What?

1494
00:48:00,058 --> 00:48:01,568
Make him funnier.

1495
00:48:01,698 --> 00:48:02,798
I'm sure he'll learn a lot today.

1496
00:48:02,798 --> 00:48:04,938
- You weren't sure, were you?
- It was...

1497
00:48:05,098 --> 00:48:08,038
- like when Jee Seok Jin...
- Yes.

1498
00:48:08,038 --> 00:48:09,808
